9. quis: this form is found only here in the lyric poems.—- amantem: sc. men—languor: lack os interest, mdg’fference, which showed itself in his silence.

13 f. simul: regularly used by Horace equivalent to simul ac. — calentis: genitive agreeing with the genitive implied in the pos- sessive pronoun that is naturally understood here, ele. mea arcana.
